Class Tuple<I extends Comparable<I>>

java.lang.Object
com.oson.tuple.Tuple<I>
Type Parameters:
I - the type of items in the tuple; must implement Comparable
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Tuple<I>>, Iterable<I>
Direct Known Subclasses:
Decad, Dodecad, Dyad, Ennead, Enneakaidecad, Hendecad, Heptad, Heptakaidecad, Hexad, Hexakaidecad, Icosad, Monad, Nullad, Octad, Octakaidecad, Pentad, Pentakaidecad, Polyad, Tetrad, Tetrakaidecad, Triad, Triskaidecad
public abstract class Tuple<I extends Comparable<I>> extends Object implements Comparable<Tuple<I>>, Iterable<I>
Abstract class representing a generic tuple of comparable items. Stores the items in a LinkedHashMap keyed by their position.

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(Tuple<I> other)
      Compares this Tuple to another Tuple using lexicographical order.

      The comparison proceeds element by element, starting from index 0, using each element's natural ordering. If all compared elements are equal, the shorter tuple is considered smaller.

      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<I extends Comparable<I>>
      Parameters:
      other - the other Tuple to compare to
      Returns:
      -1 if this tuple is lexicographically smaller, 1 if it is greater, or 0 if both tuples are equal
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if other is null
